# =====================================================
# CAMPUSEATS FRONTEND - ENVIRONMENT CONFIGURATION
# =====================================================

# Backend API URL
# For local development (default):
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# For production (Vercel/Netlify deployment):
# VITE_API_URL=https://ntu-food-backend.onrender.com
# OR if using a different backend host:
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend.railway.app

# =====================================================
# DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS:
# =====================================================
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local for local development
# 2. Never commit .env.local to git
# 3. Run backend locally on http://localhost:8000
#
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT (Vercel/Netlify):
# 1. Set VITE_API_URL in your deployment platform's dashboard:
#
#    VERCEL:
#    - Go to your project ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Environment Variables
#    - Add: VITE_API_URL = https://ntu-food-backend.onrender.com
#    - Apply to: Production, Preview, Development
#
#    NETLIFY:
#    - Go to Site settings ‚Üí Environment variables
#    - Add: VITE_API_URL = https://ntu-food-backend.onrender.com
#
# 2. Make sure your deployed backend URL is added to CORS_ORIGINS in backend/.env
#    Example: CORS_ORIGINS=https://your-app.vercel.app,https://your-app.netlify.app
#
# 3. Redeploy your frontend after setting the environment variable
# =====================================================

# =====================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING "Network Error":
# =====================================================
# If you see "Network failed. Please try again":
#
# 1. Check browser console (F12) for API configuration logs
#    Look for: "üåê API Configuration Loaded:"
#    Verify VITE_API_URL is set correctly
#
# 2. Verify backend is running and accessible:
#    Visit: https://your-backend.onrender.com/health
#    Should return: {"status":"healthy"}
#
# 3. Check CORS errors in browser console:
#    If you see CORS errors, add your frontend URL to backend CORS_ORIGINS
#
# 4. For Vercel/Netlify, rebuild after changing env vars:
#    Environment variables only take effect after redeployment
# =====================================================
